FRONT OF BILL

expand_more

Natural Gas Use

This area of your bill shows you how much natural gas your home used over the last 13 months. You can use your energy use history to:

  • Detect fluctuations
  • Identify months where you use more energy and adjust your budget
  • Forecast your energy use
  • Manage your energy use
expand_more

Monthly Energy Summary

Natural gas use is measured in thousand cubic feet and then billed according to your actual use. For more information on your specific rate, see our Energy Charges Explained page.

Payment Coupon

Detach your payment coupon from the bottom of the bill so you can include it with your payment. Or pay now online. Try the convenience of receiving your bill via email. Itâ€™s easy to make the switch in your online profile.

BACK OF BILL

expand_more

Account Information

Use this section to see how many days are in the billing period and your specific rate. More days in the billing period could result in more energy used and a higher bill, while fewer days can cut your monthly energy use and bill. Log in now to check your energy use online.

expand_more

Rate Information

The amount of energy you use and when you use it determines your rate.

expand_more

Meter Information

In this section, you can view details about the natural gas meter, including the meter number and the last time we read the meter.

expand_more

Monthly Charges Detail

This is where we keep you informed about everything included in your rate. If you have questions, call us at 800-477-5050 or monitor your account online. Log in to get started.

expand_more

News and Information

This section helps you stay up to date on Michigan energy trends and news.

expand_more

Ways to Pay Your Bill

You can choose from a variety of ways to pay your bill.
